 some regions, the rhizomes are used to treat fever, headaches, and skin conditions. The fronds are also used to treat respiratory issues such as bronchitis and asthma. The plant's medicinal properties are still being studied and researched for their potential applications in modern medicine.", "intro": "Microsorum wilkesii, also known as Wilkes' Fern, is a type of tropical fern native to Australia and the Pacific Islands, belonging to the family Polypodiaceae. This plant has been traditionally used in herbal medicine to promote wound healing, reduce inflammation, and improve immune function, making it a valuable asset in natural remedies for various health conditions. The bioactive constituents of Microsorum wilkesii include flavonoids, phenolic acids, and saponins, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. The most common herbal preparations made with this plant include teas, tinctures, and infusions, which are used to treat a range of health issues, including skin conditions, respiratory problems, and digestive issues."}